President Obama and Vice President Biden met with President Basescu of Romania to discuss the close alliance between the United States and Romania. They congratulated President Basescu on the U.S.-Romania Ballistic Missile Defense Agreement and the U.S.-Romania Joint Declaration on Strategic Partnership for the 21st Century. They thanked President Basescu for his leadership in NATO and Romania's contributions to the ISAF mission in Afghanistan. They also discussed Romania's role in supporting democracy in Europe and the Middle East, ongoing political and economic reforms in Romania, and the situation in Syria.